featured_reviews.review_id:
The masjid gate was closed during Maghrib on Jul 23rd, Sunday.
We were 12 men, who were returing from Mysuru and on the way back, we passed through this masjid. we were unable to enter the masjid as it was locked. When we called someone from inside, we were told that the watchman has locked the gate an is on leave.

My simple question to the masjid committee and management is.
The masjid in on a highway. MashaAllah, very grand masjid, it can be seen from very far away too. But it is in-accesible to people who want to pray. We finally had to jump over the fence to reach the masjid.

Really disappointed. Imagine, someone with not very strong eeman, decides to come to the masjid (House of the Almighty Allah), finds the gates closed - Who will be answerable in the day of Qayamat on that missed namaz?

Think about it.

featured_reviews.review_id:
An Oasis of Tranquility: Makkah Masjid

Makkah Masjid in Kowdenahalli, Bangaluru, India, is a hidden gem nestled amidst the bustling streets of the city. As a visitor to this beautiful mosque, I was pleasantly surprised by the serene ambiance and the architectural beauty that awaited me.

The architecture of Makkah Masjid Bangalore is a fusion of Islamic and Indo-Islamic styles, blending traditional elements with local influences. The mosque features striking minarets and a grand dome that captivate the eye.

Stepping inside, I was greeted by the expansive prayer hall, which exudes a sense of peace and devotion. The spacious hall can accommodate a large number of worshippers, and the beautifully patterned carpet adds a touch of vibrancy to the space. The lighting fixtures cast a warm glow, enhancing the spiritual ambiance of the mosque.

The management of the mosque deserves appreciation for maintaining cleanliness and providing necessary facilities for visitors. The ablution area is well-maintained and equipped with modern amenities, ensuring cleanliness and convenience for worshippers. The staff members are helpful and approachable, providing guidance and information to visitors.

While Makkah Masjid Bangalore might not be as grand in scale as its namesake in Mecca, it still holds immense significance as a place of worship for the local Muslims. The mosque serves as a spiritual hub and a gathering place for Muslims in the area, fostering a sense of unity and community among its worshippers.

One aspect that could be improved is the availability of informational materials or guided tours for non-Muslim visitors. Having more information about the history, architecture, and cultural significance of the mosque would enhance the overall experience for those unfamiliar with Islamic traditions.

In conclusion, Makkah Masjid Bangalore offers a peaceful retreat in the heart of the city, inviting visitors to experience a slice of serenity amidst the urban chaos. With its beautiful architecture and welcoming atmosphere, it serves as a testament to the diversity and rich cultural heritage of Islam. Whether you are seeking solace.

featured_reviews.review_id:
One of the few Masjid in the busy surrounding, need to go little inside from the main road to get there. The Friday Prayer timings are 1:45 pm.

Currently majority of Masjid is under construction and on completion it will look majestic. On the basement you got Wadhu Khana which is decent in size and adjacent is racks where you can keep your slippers/shoes.

Imam Sb. leads prayer at the first floor. Overall the interior of Masjid is coming up nicely.

A place to connect with a Divine and achieve mental peace and tranquility.
